dict.string: SW-DLT Official release on GitHub, avoid unknown sources!

SETTINGS ^^^^ Change the above settings as needed by your usage:
uninstall: - This will uninstall all utilities used by the shortcut. Useful if the shortcut is being removed without deleting a-Shell. Default value is 'False'

==== END OF USER SETTINGS ==== Do not edit anything below this line, or the shortcut could stop working!
GLOBAL SETTINGS INITIALIZATION
Type a range of items to download. Newest item is at first position (1). Example: 1,2,3-7,10. Commas select individual items, hyphen declares a sub-range. Both can be combined.
Uninstall mode is ON. Are you sure you want to uninstall? If not, please change the setting.
SW-DLT has been uninstalled. NOTE: It will be reinstalled & updated if started again.
Adding resources in Files > a-Shell > SW-DLT. This happens only after install/update.
The download encountered an error. Try (if applicable) using the default quality, checking website support, or reviewing provided login details.
SW-DLT ("Shortcuts Wrapper for -DL Tools") is a shortcut that makes using yt-dlp and gallery-dl fast and simple. It is powered by a-Shell, a very powerful terminal emulator for iPhone/iPad.
WORKSPACE SETUP (We download the script last so its presence also works as a signal that all previous installation steps worked)

WORKSPACE="$HOME/Documents/SW-DLT" MAIN_SCRIPT="$WORKSPACE/SW_DLT.py" VENV="$WORKSPACE/SW-DLT-ENV/"
if [ ! -f $MAIN_SCRIPT ] || [ ! -d $VENV ] then mkdir -p $WORKSPACE echo "CONTINUE_INSTALL" fi

clear hideKeyboard echo "Please wait..." python -m venv $HOME/Documents/SW-DLT/SW-DLT-ENV/ source $HOME/Documents/SW-DLT/SW-DLT-ENV/bin/activate pip install chardet requests -q --disable-pip-version-check pip install yt-dlp -q --disable-pip-version-check pip install gallery-dl -q --disable-pip-version-check curl -sL https://net00-1.github.io/SW-DLT/api/content/SW_DLT.py -o $HOME/Documents/SW-DLT/SW_DLT.py deactivate open shortcuts:// clear && cd exit

LATEST_VERSION="https://net00-1.github.io/SW-DLT/api/updates/latest.json" WORKSPACE="$HOME/Documents/SW-DLT" LAST_CHECK_TS="$WORKSPACE/shortcut_update_ts.txt" CURRENT_DATE=$(date +%s) CURRENT_VERSION="￼"
if [ ! -f $LAST_CHECK_TS ] then echo 0 > $LAST_CHECK_TS fi
TS_DATE=$(cat $LAST_CHECK_TS) DATE_DIFF=$(($CURRENT_DATE - $TS_DATE))
if [ $((DATE_DIFF / 86400)) -ge 1 ] then VER_CHECK=$(curl -sL $LATEST_VERSION) date +%s > $LAST_CHECK_TS if [ "$CURRENT_VERSION" != $(echo $VER_CHECK | jq -r ".version") ] then echo $VER_CHECK fi fi
